You are working in `/Users/ryanr/Code/hevy-planner` on the `main` branch. Apply the following code quality fixes from a review. Make ALL changes listed below.

## 1. Extract `sseErrorCard` helper in `src/index.ts`

The pattern `sseResponse(patchElements(\`<div class="card"><p style="color:var(--orange)">${escapeHtml(msg)}</p></div>\`, { selector, mode }))` appears ~12 times. Create a helper near the other utility functions (near `sseResponse`, `patchElements`):

```typescript
function sseErrorCard(msg: string, selector = "#content", mode: "inner" | "prepend" | "append" = "prepend"): Response {
  return sseResponse(
    patchElements(
      `<div class="card"><p style="color:var(--orange)">${escapeHtml(msg)}</p></div>`,
      { selector, mode }
    )
  );
}
```

Then replace all instances of that pattern with calls to `sseErrorCard(msg, selector, mode)`. Be careful: some use `mode: "inner"`, some `mode: "prepend"`. Make sure to preserve the correct mode for each call site. Some error messages are already escaped, some aren't ΓÇö the helper always escapes, so don't double-escape.

## 2. Extract shared validate helper in `src/index.ts`

`handleValidateProgram` and `handleValidateImportProgram` are near-identical. Create:

```typescript
function validateAndRespond(
  programJsonStr: string | undefined,
  selector: string,
  renderTemplates: (templates: WeekTemplate[]) => string,
  fallback?: string
): Response {
  const jsonStr = programJsonStr || fallback;
  if (!jsonStr) {
    return sseErrorCard("No program JSON provided.", selector, "inner");
  }
  // ... parse, validate, return errors or success fragment
}
```

Then both handlers become thin wrappers calling `validateAndRespond`.

## 3. Extract shared template card builder

In `src/fragments/setup.ts`, `templateSelectionFragment` and in `src/fragments/program.ts`, `importTemplateSelectionFragment` share the same sort + map + card HTML logic. Extract a shared function. The only difference is the `data-on:click` attribute per card.

Create a shared helper (in whichever file makes more sense, or in a new shared fragment util):

```typescript
export function renderTemplateGrid(
  templates: WeekTemplate[],
  cardAttrs: (templateId: string) => string
): string {
  const sorted = [...templates].sort((a, b) => (a.sortOrder ?? 0) - (b.sortOrder ?? 0));
  const cards = sorted.map(t => `<div class="template-card" ${cardAttrs(t.id)}>
  <div class="template-name">${escapeHtml(t.name)}</div>
  ${t.description ? `<div class="template-desc">${escapeHtml(t.description)}</div>` : ""}
</div>`).join("\n    ");
  return `<div class="template-grid">\n    ${cards}\n    </div>`;
}
```

Then both `templateSelectionFragment` and `importTemplateSelectionFragment` call this with their specific click handler.

## 4. Remove dead `prescribedExercises` from `CompletedItemData`

In `src/fragments/today.ts`:
- Remove `prescribedExercises` from the `CompletedItemData` interface
- Remove the `RoutineExercise` import if no longer used

In `src/index.ts` (`handleTodaySSE`):
- Remove `prescribedExercises` from the completed data mapping
- Remove it from the daily routine unshift too

## 5. Remove dead `getWorkoutsSince` from `src/hevy/client.ts`

Delete the entire `getWorkoutsSince` method ΓÇö it's never called.

## 6. Fix `deleteWebhookSubscription` to use `this.request()`

In `src/hevy/client.ts`, change `deleteWebhookSubscription` to use the shared `this.request()` method instead of raw `fetch`. Read the existing `this.request` method carefully to understand how it works. You may need to handle the case where the response body is empty (204 No Content) ΓÇö check if `this.request` tries to parse JSON and adjust accordingly.

## 7. Merge two Maps into one in `performSync`

In `src/index.ts` `performSync`, replace `workoutDateMap` and `workoutExercisesMap` with a single:
```typescript
const workoutInfo = new Map<string, { date: string; exercisesJson: string }>();
```
Update the consumers to read from this single map.

## 8. Extract `toLocalDate` helper

The pattern:
```typescript
tz ? new Date(startTime).toLocaleDateString("en-CA", { timeZone: tz }) : startTime.slice(0, 10)
```
appears twice in `performSync`. Extract it as a utility function. Put it in `src/utils/date.ts` or similar. Also refactor `todayString` to use it if possible.

Wait ΓÇö first check if there's already a date utils file. If `todayString` is defined somewhere, put `toLocalDate` next to it.

## 9. Fix UTC timezone bug in `syncButton`

In `src/fragments/today.ts`, `syncButton` calls `new Date(lastSyncAt).toLocaleString()` without a timezone, which in Workers always uses UTC. Thread the `tz` parameter through:
- Add `tz?: string` parameter to `syncButton`
- Use `new Date(lastSyncAt).toLocaleString("en-US", { timeZone: tz ?? "UTC" })`
- Update the caller in `src/index.ts` `handleTodaySSE` to pass `tz`

## 10. Batch DB writes

In `src/index.ts` `performSync`, replace the sequential `markQueueItemCompleted` loop with `db.batch(...)`:
```typescript
await db.batch(matches.map(match => {
  const info = workoutInfo.get(match.workoutId);
  return db.prepare("UPDATE queue_items SET status = 'completed', completed_date = ?, hevy_workout_id = ?, hevy_workout_data = ? WHERE id = ?")
    .bind(info?.date ?? todayString(tz), match.workoutId, info?.exercisesJson ?? null, match.queueItemId);
}));
```

In `src/index.ts` `activateProgram`, batch the `upsertExerciseTemplateMapping` calls and `upsertRoutineMapping` calls similarly.

In `src/storage/queries.ts`, batch `clearMappings`:
```typescript
export async function clearMappings(db: D1Database, userId: string): Promise<void> {
  await db.batch([
    db.prepare("DELETE FROM exercise_template_mappings WHERE user_id = ?").bind(userId),
    db.prepare("DELETE FROM routine_mappings WHERE user_id = ?").bind(userId),
  ]);
}
```

## 11. Fix test fixtures

In test files under `test/`, add `hevy_workout_data: null` to all `QueueItemRow` test fixtures that are missing it. Search for test files that construct QueueItemRow objects.

## 12. Fix non-null assertion in `activateProgram`

Replace:
```typescript
const template = program.weekTemplates.find((t) => t.id === templateId)!;
```
With:
```typescript
const template = program.weekTemplates.find((t) => t.id === templateId);
if (!template) throw new Error(`Week template "${templateId}" not found in program`);
```

## Important conventions
- D1 queries use prepared statements (no raw string interpolation)
- Import `escapeHtml`, `escapeAttr` from `src/utils/html`
- Domain functions are pure: data in, data out
- Existing test patterns: use vitest

## After all changes
Run `npm run test` to verify all tests pass. Fix any that break.
Then run `git add -A && git diff --cached --stat` so I can see what changed.

